# decision-golden.json.meta — provenance sidecar for decision-golden.json (issue #400, R5).
#
# Captured by running the PRE-CHANGE (byte-identical-passthrough) callers —
# drain_agent_pr_create (lib-auth.sh), the PASS-path chp_approve site
# (autonomous-review.sh), and the merge path chp_merge site
# (autonomous-review.sh) — against a stubbed CHP provider with the three write
# leaves returning controllable rc/output, on the FIRST TDD commit of the #400
# W1e branch (before the abstract-contract rewrite landed). Values are
# CALLER-observable DECISIONS (log line substrings, transition edges, whether
# a manual-merge notification / auto-merge-failure marker / verdict trailer
# was posted, whether the merge-failure excerpt matched on the first 500
# chars) — not gh argv (that is proven byte-identical by
# test-chp-pr-lifecycle.sh's golden trace, which is re-pinned to the NEW
# leaf-emitted argv in the same PR).
#
# Fixture classes (each caller run once per class):
#   chp_create_pr.rc0 — leaf succeeds; broker logs the success line.
#   chp_create_pr.rc1 — leaf fails; broker logs the "brokered PR create ...
#                       failed" WARN, returns 0 (the no-PR retry re-queues).
#   chp_approve.rc0   — leaf succeeds; wrapper falls through to the merge/
#                       no-auto-close branching (no manual-merge fallback).
#   chp_approve.rc1   — leaf fails; wrapper posts manual-merge notification
#                       + reviewing->approved transition + exit 0.
#   chp_merge.rc0     — leaf succeeds; wrapper emits merge-success metrics +
#                       the reviewing,autonomous->approved multi-remove
#                       transition; NO PR-comment marker, NO pending-dev
#                       verdict trailer.
#   chp_merge.rc1     — leaf fails; wrapper captures the first-500-chars
#                       failure excerpt into a PR comment marker + emits the
#                       merge-failure metrics + posts the pending-dev
#                       verdict trailer via the [INV-77] retry channel.
#                       (excerpt_first_500_chars_match asserts the leaf's
#                       stdout/stderr is preserved through the seam so the
#                       excerpt content matches the pre-#400 byte-identical
#                       leaf output for the same failure text.)
#
# Regenerate (only if the OLD pre-#400 semantics are ever in dispute):
# checkout the commit immediately before #400's leaf rewrite, source
# lib-auth.sh / autonomous-review.sh under the parity harness in
# tests/unit/test-w1e-chp-write-parity.sh with the parity fixture's chp_*
# overrides, and re-run.
